column5: Heard a few rumers - is this a good lake for waleyes? What time of the year and where? Thanks the worm dunker
Great LAke,Right Now,Rowans Ravine on East Side and South,Bouncers and Crawlers,Good Luck,Wish I Was There!

I live on the lake and fish it at least 3 days a week. It is a lake where you will not get big numbers but you can catch big fish. I personally have catch a 14 pounder and at least 8 over 10 pounds (my first year of walleye fishing). It depends one the time of year you fish the lake. In summer there is an super crank bit, in the fall it is leeaches and live bait rigs over the major points. Slow presentation!!! In the spring it is either the north end which is real rocky or the south end!! Take CareWilliam
